{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, we hope to assist in showing whether RL can prove to be useful for FLP research and practitioners.",
    "Facility Layout ProblemsThe central objective of Facility Layout Problems involves determining the optimal spatial arrangement of workstations, departments, machines, or equipment within a facility.",
    "This arrangement profoundly influences factors such as material handling expenses, production time, worker movement, and overall facility utilisation.",
    "FLPs encompass identifying the most favourable positioning of these components while adhering to constraints such as space limitations, safety regulations, and workflow prerequisites [16,17].",
    "Typically, one central element of an FLP is to minimise the transport intensity between facilities, given their pairwise flow relationships and distances."
  ]
}